          "user_id": 314328453,
          "body": "Hi Alma, I read through your explanation this morning. Very appreciated, thanks! I now understand better why they said nowadays stock prices do not really represent the value of a company... Between indexes, futures, and options, there's so much distortion it's insane :D\n\nI wanted to ask: when you say for example that something is \"vol of vol\", is vol = volatility for both, or one is volatility and the other volume? Sorry, I get a bit confused because I've seen some people use \"vol\" for \"volume\"",
